ACID vs BASE ACID (traditional SQL databases) Ensures strong consistency and reliability:

Atomicity
Consistency
Isolation
Durability

Used by: MySQL, PostgreSQL, Oracle, SQL Server, etc.

BASE (mostly NoSQL / distributed systems) Designed for horizontal scaling and high availability:
Basically
Available
Soft-state
Eventually consistent

Used by: Cassandra, DynamoDB, Riak, Couchbase, etc.